JOHANNESBURG - SuperSport United and Maritzburg United have agreed terms for the permanent move of Zimbabwean international striker Evans Rusike with immediate effect. Rusike has signed a three-year deal with Matsatsantsa. SuperSport United CEO Stanley Matthews, “We have been watching Evans with great interest over the last few years at Maritzburg. The 27-year-old forward has netted over 20 goals during his two and a half year stay at the team of choice and represented his national team in the 2017 Afcon tournament. He is currently 3rd on the PSL’s goal scoring charts with seven goals so far this season. SuperSport United CEO Stanley Matthews, “We have been watching Evans with great interest over the last few years at Maritzburg. He has all the makings of a great striker with blistering pace, great skill and he can finish in the box. Rusike, "I know I have to prove myself to the coach and management of SuperSport and I will give my best to boost the team into the Top 8 this season.” "We are thrilled to announce his signing and look forward to him making a meaningful contribution for us over the next few years.” READ: Disastrous SuperSport United run continues Rusike said: “SuperSport is a great club. They have achieved a lot in their short history, especially in the Cups.  They have also shown that they can get players to Europe and it remains my dream to play in Europe. "I know I have to prove myself to the coach and management of SuperSport and I will give my best to boost the team into the Top 8 this season.” .@SuperSportFC and @MaritzburgUtd have agreed terms for the permanent move of Zimbabwean international striker Evans Rusike with immediate effect.
		
